DL LAB ASSIGNMENT 1

This code performs PCA (Principal Component Analysis) on the Iris dataset to reduce dimensions and visualize the data in 2D. Since you‚Äôre studying deep learning/data science, this is a classic dimensionality reduction technique used before modeling or for visualization.

What PCA means (concept)

PCA = Principal Component Analysis
It reduces a dataset with many features into fewer features while keeping most of the important information.

Example:
Your Iris dataset has 4 features:

sepal length
sepal width
petal length
petal width

PCA converts these into new variables called principal components:

PC1 ‚Üí captures maximum variance
PC2 ‚Üí captures second highest variance

These are combinations of original features, but they retain most of the data patterns.

Why PCA is used

Uses of PCA:

Reduce number of features
Remove unnecessary dimensions
Faster training
Better visualization
Removes correlation between features

For machine learning/deep learning:
PCA helps simplify data before classification.

