DL LAB ASSIGNMENT 3
Concept Used
K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

KNN means:

K = number of nearest neighbors

The algorithm classifies a new data point by checking the nearest existing points.

Simple idea:

It predicts based on nearby similar data.

Example

Suppose a flower has:

petal length = 5.2
petal width = 1.8

KNN checks nearest flowers in dataset and assigns the majority class.

How KNN works

Steps:

Store training data
Take new test point
Calculate distance from all points
Find nearest K points
Majority vote
Assign class
Formula used

Distance is usually Euclidean:

d=
‚ąĎ
i=1
n
	‚Äč

(x
i
	‚Äč

‚ąíy
i
	‚Äč

)
2
	‚Äč


This calculates distance between two points.

