Concept Used
Naive Bayes

Naive Bayes is based on:

Bayes Theorem
P(A‚ą£B)=
P(B)
P(B‚ą£A)P(A)
	‚Äč

P(A)
P(B‚ą£A)
P(B‚ą£¬¨A)
P(A‚ą£B)=
P(B)
P(B‚ą£A)P(A)
	‚Äč

‚Čą0.68,P(B)‚Čą0.25
P(B)=0.25
P(B|A)P(A)=0.17
P(A|B)~0.68
Posterior = useful evidence / total evidence

Meaning:

Probability of event A given B.

In your case

It predicts whether news is:

Fake
Real

based on words:

breaking
shocking
exclusive
Why called ‚ÄúNaive‚ÄĚ?

Because it assumes all features are independent.

Example:

It assumes:

breaking
shocking
exclusive

do not affect each other.

That assumption is called naive.

Your Problem

