DL LAB ASSIGNMENT 10
This code performs weather forecasting using LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) to predict future temperature values based on past temperature data.

It is a time-series prediction problem using deep learning.

This is very similar to your stock prediction code, but here it predicts temperature instead of stock prices.

Main concept used
Time Series Forecasting

Time series means:

Data collected over time.

Examples:

temperature
rainfall
stock prices
traffic flow
electricity demand

Since weather changes over time, previous temperature helps predict future temperature.

Why LSTM?

LSTM is designed for sequential/time-dependent data.

Weather depends on previous days.

Example:

Tomorrow‚Äôs temperature depends on previous temperature trends.

What your code does

It:

loads weather data
normalizes temperature values
creates sequences
trains LSTM
predicts temperature
compares actual vs predicted values
Step-by-step explanation
